               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Taʾammǝra Māryām “Miracles of Mary” (fols. 3ra-54ra)
 I-1) Maṣḥafa
                     śǝrʿāt, Introductory rite of al-Muʿallaqah (fols. 3ra-7va)
 I-2)
                     Introductory exhortation (fols. 7ra-10vb)
 I-3) ʾƎsaggǝd laki
                     wa-ʾǝweddǝsaki … “I worship Thee…” (fols. 10vb-12rb)
 I-4) Taʾammǝra Māryām:
                     29 partly numbered miracles (fols. 12rb-53rb, 54ra)
 I-5) ʾAkkonu bǝʾsi…
                     “Does not the man…” (distributed among the miracles of Mary, fols.
                     15rb-52vb)
 
 Additiones 1-2.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>Text I-2 includes the hymns:</note>
                     <note>- ʾO-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä qǝddǝst dǝngǝl ba-kǝlʾe Māryām ʾǝmmu la-ʾIyasus kahāli …
                        "O my Lady, Holy Two-fold Virgin Mary, mother of Jesus the Almighty ..."
                           (<locus target="#9rb">9rb-</locus>va),</note>
                     <note>- salām laki ʾo-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä Māryām dǝngǝl ʾǝmma bǝrhān wa-ʾǝmma nädd...
                        "Salutation to you, o my Lady, Virgin Mary, Mother of the Light and Mother
                        of the Flame ..." (<locus from="9va" to="10vb">9va-10vb</locus>).</note>
                     <note>Some miracles are not numbered. The first miracle is followed by the
                        hymn: Sobä ṣäḥafä Däqsǝyos täʾamriha ʿǝludä ... "When Däqsǝyos wrote the
                        collection of her miracles ..." (<locus target="#14va">14va</locus>).</note>
                     <note>Text I-5 comprises 25 strophes which are strophes 2-10, 12-27 according
                        to GrohHymn pp. 336-53.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
